HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1495
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Komatsu Chattanooga
Manufacturing Operations on the occasion of its
fortieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those Tennessee businesses that are celebrating significant milestones this year; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable entity is Komatsu Chattanooga Manufacturing
Operations, which celebrates its fortieth anniversary this year, a commendable milestone for this
notable business; and
WHEREAS, opened in February 1985, Komatsu Chattanooga Manufacturing Operations
was Chattanooga's first Japanese manufacturing plant and Komatsu's first plant in the United
States; and
WHEREAS, Komatsu Chattanooga Manufacturing Operations is a part of Komatsu
America Corp., which is the U.S. subsidiary of Komatsu Ltd., one of the world's largest
manufacturers and suppliers of earth-moving equipment, consisting of construction, mining, and
compact construction markets, as well as forklift and forestry markets in the U.S.; and
WHEREAS, the success of the Komatsu Chattanooga Manufacturing Operations is
based on two guiding principles: the manufacture of competitive high-quality products that
deliver maximum customer satisfaction and community involvement in Chattanooga; and
WHEREAS, the plant has been committed to its employees and has actively participated
and supported a variety of community endeavors, including exhibit sponsorships at the world-
acclaimed Tennessee Aquarium, long-term support of local United Way activities, and
partnership with the Orange Grove Center in Chattanooga; and
HJR1495
018245
- 1 -

WHEREAS, for four decades, Komatsu Chattanooga Manufacturing Operations has
provided exceptional service to its customers and the Chattanooga community, and it is fitting
that the business be recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Komatsu Chattanooga Manufacturing Operations
on the occasion of its fortieth anniversary, wishing this esteemed business much continued
success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
